<rss version="2.0"><channel><title>守护者</title><description>卫报全文RSS。获取更多全文RSS：https://feedx.net</description><link/> https://theguardian.com <item><title><![CDATA[Matteo Messina Denaro, ‘last godfather’ of Sicilian mafia, dies after long illness, reports say]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/sep/25/matteo-messina-denaro-last-godfather-of-sicilian-mafia-cosa-nostra-dies-after-long-illness]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-09-25T04:42:26Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/9b025da8aa02f5297e4a5d3e411ee328f9698a6e/0_640_2863_1718 /master/2863.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=a04cb8b187cd3ab583b9a0b7cd1fbfee&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;Matteo Messina Denaro 于 1 月 16 日在巴勒莫被捕后的照片。&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;Matteo Messina据意大利媒体报道，西西里黑手党的“最后教父”德纳罗因长期患病而去世，他被指控策划了科萨·诺斯特拉 (Cosa Nostra) 犯下的一些最令人发指的罪行。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;1 月，德纳罗，61 岁，自 1993 年以来一直躲藏起来，&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/jan/16/italy-most-wanted-mafia-boss-matteo-messina-德纳罗被捕&quot;>;在巴勒莫的一家私人诊所被捕&lt;/a>;，他在那里以假名安德里亚·博纳菲德 (Andrea Bonafede) 定期接受肿瘤治疗。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;8 月，他被从” p>; &lt;p>;绰号 Diabolik 或 &lt;em>;U Siccu&lt;/em>;（瘦子），德纳罗于 1962 年出生于西西里岛的卡斯特尔韦特拉诺。他的父亲是一位有权势的科萨·诺斯特拉 (Cosa Nostra) 老板，德纳罗在家族企业中蓬勃发展，在废物、风能和零售领域建立一个价值数十亿欧元的非法帝国。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;2002 年，他因亲自杀害或下令谋杀数十人而被定罪并缺席判处终身监禁。 &lt;/p>; &lt;p>;这名曾臭名昭著地声称：“我一个人填满了一座墓地”的歹徒在逃期间，显然一直保持着奢华的生活方式，这要归功于几位资助者，据检察官称，这些资助者包括：政治家和商人。他以穿着昂贵的西装、戴着劳力士和雷朋太阳镜而闻名。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;由于几乎完全没有近期照片，寻找德纳罗的任务变得很复杂。意大利当局仅利用 20 世纪 80 年代末和 90 年代初拍摄的几张身份照片，利用最新的计算机技术和 &lt;a href=&quot;x-gu://list/mobile.guardianapis.com 提供的信息，以数字方式重建了他的外貌。 /international/lists/tag/world/mafia&quot;>;黑手党&lt;/a>;叛徒。&lt;/p>; &lt;figure data-media-id=&quot;7a064088ab77e18383c2969444f183fca89959d6&quot;>; &lt;img src=&quot;https://media.guim.co. uk/7a064088ab77e18383c2969444f183fca89959d6/6_0_737_442/500.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;警方发布的年轻德纳罗的合成图像和计算机生成的老年人图像。&quot; width=&quot;500&quot; height=&quot;300&quot;>; &lt;figcaption>; &lt;span>;警方发布的年轻德纳罗的合成图像和计算机生成的老年人图像。&lt;/span>; &lt;span>;照片：美联社&lt;/多年来，已有数十人因身份错误而被逮捕。 2019 年，宪兵宪兵突击搜查西西里岛一家医院，逮捕了一名来自卡斯特尔韦特拉诺的男子，该男子正在神经科康复中。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;30 年来，每当调查人员似乎更接近目标时，德纳罗就会消失离开。就像幽灵一样，他会在世界各地消失并重新出现。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;逮捕前的周五，宪兵队收到了决定性的举报：1 月 16 日上午 8 点左右，嫌疑人将返回诊所接受检查。治疗。&lt;/p>; &lt;aside>; &lt;p>;&lt;span>;相关：&lt;/span>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/feb/02/like-being-on- a-rollercoaster-the-man-who-caught-sicilys-last-mafia-boss&quot;>;“就像坐过山车一样”：抓住了西西里岛最后一个黑手党老大的人&lt;/a>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/aside>; &lt; p>;被捕后，德纳罗被转移到意大利中部城市拉奎拉的一所戒备森严的监狱，他在那里继续接受癌症治疗。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“你逮捕我只是因为我的病，”德纳罗与其他西西里黑手党头目一样，德纳罗一直拒绝与当局合作并揭露科萨诺斯特拉的罪行。据黑手党线人和检察官称，他掌握了西西里黑手党实施的一些最残暴谋杀案的关键，其中包括杀死传奇反黑手党治安官乔瓦尼·法尔科内和保罗·博尔塞利诺的炸弹袭击。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;调查人员现在担心西西里黑手党的最后一位教父已经把这些秘密带进了坟墓。&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Mon, 25 Sep 2023 12:52:01 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[No 10 increasingly concerned AI could be used to create bioweapons]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2023/sep/25/ai-bioweapons-rishi-sunak-safety]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-09-25T04:00:18Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/62090313f43554650a6091528f1fabdfca085cb3/0_987_6368_3823 /master/6368.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=13bf445a7f1ff239c5a2f3c5c1813506&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;官员们越来越担心这种可能性，以及需要通过监管来缓解这些可能性&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;随着唐宁街对下一代技术进步力量的担忧日益加深，对犯罪分子或恐怖分子可能利用人工智能造成大规模杀伤性的担忧将成为世界领导人峰会讨论的主要议题。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;英国官员在 11 月的人工智能安全峰会之前，他们正在世界各地巡演，希望就一份联合声明达成共识，该声明将警告流氓行为者利用该技术造成大规模死亡的危险。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;总理里希·苏纳克 (Rishi Sunak) 周围的人担心，这项技术很快就会强大到足以帮助个人制造生物武器或完全逃避人类控制。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;官员们越来越担心这种可能性，以及需要通过监管来缓解这些可能性在最近与高级技术主管讨论之后。上周，一封具有里程碑意义的信件背后的科学家呼吁暂停开发强大的人工智能系统，他表示科技高管&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2023/sep/21/ai-focused-tech-公司-locked-race-bottom-warns-mit-professor-max-tegmark&quot;>;私下同意中断的概念&lt;/a>;，但感觉他们陷入了与竞争对手的人工智能军备竞赛。&lt;/p>; &lt;p >;一位了解峰会对话情况的人士表示：“峰会的重点是警告‘前沿人工智能’的风险，这也是唐宁街目前最关注的问题。”前沿人工智能是一个术语，用来指最先进的人工智能模型，这些模型可能危险到足以对人类生命构成威胁。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;苏纳克一直是&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian. com/technology/2023/may/26/rishi-sunak-races-to-tighten-rules-for-ai-amid-fears-of-existential-risk&quot;>;警告&lt;/a>;人工智能对一些人造成的风险几个月来，敦促国际社会采取&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2023/may/18/uk-will-lead-on-guard-rails-to-limit-dangers-of -ai-says-rishi-sunak&quot;>;护栏&lt;/a>;，以防止其被滥用。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;周五，副总理奥利弗·道登 (Oliver Dowden) 在联合国大会上告诉世界领导人：“由于科技公司和非国家行为者在人工智能领域往往具有国家规模的影响力和突出地位，因此这一挑战需要一种新形式的多边主义。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;官员们对人工智能模型的最新发展感到震惊。去年，一个人工智能工具只花了六个小时&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theverge.com/2022/3/17/22983197/ai-new-possible-chemical-weapons-generative-models-vx&quot;>;提出&lt;/a>; 40,000 种不同的潜在致命分子，其中一些与 VX 类似，VX 是有史以来开发出的最有效的神经毒剂。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;今年早些时候，研究人员发现了 ChatGPT &lt;a href=&quot;https:/ /gizmodo.com/gpt4-open-ai-chatbot-task-rabbit-chatgpt-1850227471&quot;>;能够对人类撒谎&lt;/a>;以实现特定目标。人工智能聊天机器人告诉一个人是一个有视力障碍的人需要帮助才能访问网站，然后说服一个人解决“验证码”工具，该工具旨在清除在线机器人。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;政府消息人士担心犯罪分子或恐怖分子可以使用人工智能帮助他们计算出生物武器的成分，然后将它们送到机器人实验室，在那里可以在没有任何人类监督的情况下混合和调度它们。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;这种风险很快就会增加一些人认为，随着公司已经花费数亿英镑购买更强大的处理器来训练下一代人工智能工具，人工智能的发展呈指数级增长。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;另一个令人担忧的问题是“通用人工智能”这一术语的出现。这是指能够以人类或高于人类水平自主执行任何任务的人工智能系统，并且可能对人类构成生存风险。有人担心 AGI 还需要几年的时间。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;然而，存在主义的 AGI 风险方法也已&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.dair-institute.org/about/&quot; >;受到人工智能专家的批评&lt;/a>;，他们认为这种威胁被夸大了，导致人们担心虚假信息被忽视，并且通过引入排除新来者的监管而冒着巩固领先科技公司权力的风险。上周，一位高级科技高管告诉美国立法者，&lt;a href=&quot;https://viewer.gutools.co.uk/technology/2023/sep/12/us-senate-ai-hearings-microsoft-nvidia&quot;>;无法控制的 AGI 的概念是“科幻小说”。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;尽管如此，Sunak 希望利用这次峰会将注意力集中在存在风险上，而不是人工智能可以用来制造 Deepfake 的更直接的可能性。托尼·布莱尔研究所 (Tony Blair Institute) 首席政策策略师 Benedict Macon-Cooney 最近发布了一份关于人工智能的政策报告，他表示： “生物安全、自主武器系统——这些都是我们必须确保得到答案的问题。人工智能行业的许多人告诉政治家这些是真正的风险。政客们被提出了这个问题，他们必须做出回应。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;消息人士称，总理也以外交上可能的方式为指导。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;多位世界领导人&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2023/sep/15/rishi-sunak-considers-banning-chinese-officials-from-half-of-ai-summit&quot;>;将参加峰会&lt;/a>;，包括加拿大总理贾斯汀·特鲁多和法国总统埃马纽埃尔·马克龙。英国已邀请中国参加，但出于对中国在西方民主国家从事间谍活动的担忧，正在考虑允许北京官员仅参加峰会的部分活动。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;英国官员最近几天一直在世界各地访问，在峰会结束时测试某种形式协议的范围。英国渴望获得一份供领导人随后签署的正式声明，并承诺在未来举行其他此类峰会。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;在如此多元化的国家之间达成协议的最佳方式，官员们认为，重点是关注非国家行为者，而不是试图决定各国如何开发自己的技术。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;唐宁街正在斥资 1 亿英镑组建新的人工智能工作组，以帮助测试开发的算法。英国官员计划利用这次峰会敦促世界各地的公司将其人工智能工具发送到英国进行评估，然后再更广泛地推广。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;道登周五表示：“只有民族国家才能保证：最重要的国家安全问题已经得到缓解。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;政府发言人表示，人工智能“具有改变我们生活方方面面的巨大潜力”，并且已经成立了前沿人工智能工作组，以确保该技术的安全开发负责任地，人工智能安全峰会也考虑了“一系列可能的风险”。&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Mon, 25 Sep 2023 12:22:01 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Russian news outlet in Latvia believes European state behind phone hack]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/sep/25/latvia-russia-meduza-phone-hack-galina-timchenko]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-09-25T04:00:18Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/27ca62ce6b636a6c1af265fe1f67461603d91​​964/0_262_4173_2504 /master/4173.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=54b5836ef0ff705d498dfa2aa9278676&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;一群穿着冬衣的白人，大部分是年轻人，站在一棵光秃秃的树旁边，举着牌子，包括让弗拉基米尔·普京看起来像阿道夫·希特勒的设计。中间，一名年轻男子抱着一名正在哭泣的年轻女子。&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;一家独立的俄罗斯新闻媒体，其创始人今年早些时候在德国被军事级间谍软件黑客攻击，该媒体表示，它认为某个欧洲国家正在遭受黑客攻击。最有可能&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2023/sep/13/exiled- Russian-journalist-galina-timchenko-reportedly-hacked-using-nso-group-spyware&quot;>;背后网络攻击&lt;/a>;，引发了有关欧盟成员国可能对记者使用列入黑名单的网络武器的棘手问题。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Galina Timchenko 和 Meduza 的创始人兼现任主编 Ivan Kolpakov，&lt; a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/media/2023/jan/26/Russia-outlaws-meduza-in-attempt-to-stamp-out-independent-news&quot;>;拉脱维亚独立俄罗斯新闻被克里姆林宫取缔的媒体称，新的间接证据表明，今年早些时候，蒂姆琴科的手机在柏林遭到黑客攻击，而新的间接证据表明，一个欧盟国家可能是幕后黑手。这起事件发生在 2 月份，就在她参加流亡俄罗斯人的一次会议之前不久。 &lt;/p>; &lt;p>;这一消息促使一位欧洲议会议员表示，政府似乎越来越多地使用类似于东德秘密警察斯塔西曾经使用的监视方法，但没有适当的监督。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>; >; &lt;aside>; &lt;p>;&lt;span>;相关：&lt;/span>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/aug/17/berlin-prosecutor-probes-possible-poisoning-of -Russian-journalist&quot;>;柏林检察官调查俄罗斯记者可能中毒事件&lt;/a>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/aside>; &lt;p>;Timchenko 在收到苹果公司的警告时首先收到了有关黑客攻击的警报。 《卫报》随后获悉，至少四名其他俄罗斯记者（其中三人在拉脱维亚拥有手机）也收到了同样的警告。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;多伦多大学公民实验室和 Access Now 稍后进行了一项调查高度确定地确认 Timchenko 的手机（使用拉脱维亚国家代码）被 Pegasus 的政府用户黑客攻击，Pegasus 是以色列 NSO 集团制造的复杂间谍软件。成功部署后，Pegasus 可以破解任何手机，甚至将手机变成远程监听设备。&lt;/p>; &lt;figure data-media-id=&quot;709b7e2830628c6d656c2bb1e3d21d7063723210&quot;>; &lt;img src=&quot;https://media.guim. co.uk/709b7e2830628c6d656c2bb1e3d21d7063723210/0_28_2855_1713/1000.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;一位戴着墨镜、留着齐下巴棕色头发和刘海的中年白人妇女的特写镜头。&quot; width=&quot;1000&quot; height=&quot;600&quot;>; &lt;figcaption>; &lt;span>;Meduza 首席执行官 Galina Timchenko 于 2019 年 6 月 8 日在莫斯科法院大楼外接受采访。&lt;/span>; &lt;span>;照片：Tatyana Makeyeva/Reuters&lt;/span>; &lt;/figcaption>; &lt;/figure>; &lt;p>;Timchenko 最初表示，她相信针对她的袭击源自俄罗斯，并指出克里姆林宫自 2014 年以来一直在追捕和跟踪她和 Meduza 的同事。 ，包括使用复杂的网络攻击。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;但 Citizen Lab 和 Access Now 的研究人员表示，他们不相信俄罗斯是 NSO 的客户。独立研究人员还证实，拉脱维亚、爱沙尼亚和德国境内的机构是 NSO 集团的客户，并且可以访问间谍软件。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;在拉脱维亚生活了近十年的 Timchenko 表示，她现在相信欧盟国家可能将她作为目标，希望从她与最近离开俄罗斯的其他俄罗斯记者的交流中获取信息。无论如何，她称任何国家针对她都是一种“昂贵的快乐”。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Timchenko 和 Kolpakov 指出去年年底出现的紧张局势，当时 Meduza 是第一家公开辩护的拉脱维亚媒体另一家独立的俄罗斯媒体集团，倾向自由主义的 TV Rain 广播公司，在 &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2022/dec/06/rain-Russian-tv 后被驱逐出波罗的海国家-station-in-latvia-loses-licence-over-ukraine-war-coverage&quot;>;一家国家广播监管机构指控其对拉脱维亚国家安全构成威胁。&lt;/a>;&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;该广播公司受到批评因为展示了包括被占领的克里米亚在内的俄罗斯地图，以及一名主播决定将俄罗斯军队称为“我们的军队”。 TV Rain 也没有按照要求向观众提供拉脱维亚语字幕。该广播公司被迫将其业务转移到荷兰，并引发了当时媒体报道的“&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.reuters.com/business/media-telecom/latvia-cancels-license- Russiann” -independent-television-station-tv-rain-2022-12-06/&quot;>;拉脱维亚多数群体与拉脱维亚俄语少数群体之间的裂痕日益扩大&lt;/a>;。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Meduza 记者表示，他们发表了&lt;a href=&quot;https://meduza.io/en/feature/2022/12/06/meduza-s-statement-regarding-the-replication-of-tv-rain-s-latvian-broadcasting-license&quot;>;支持新闻自由的公开信&lt;/a>;，批评拉脱维亚的决定，并有 300 名支持者签署。它称监管机构的举动“不公平、错误且与官方违规行为不成比例”。&lt;/p>; &lt;figure data-media-id=&quot;9548bf037db0ccb4005a867e919b9530a0ab1d17&quot;>; &lt;img src=&quot;https://media.guim.co.uk /9548bf037db0ccb4005a867e919b9530a0ab1d17/0_182_3500_2101/1000.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;一张在一间宽敞的室内房间拍摄的照片，天花板低矮，木椽子整齐，荧光灯，灰色工业地毯和大木桌。木柱上挂着黑色雨衣，前景中撑着一把黑色雨伞。两个白人似乎正在聊天，其中一个坐在一张桌子旁，另一个站在桌子旁边。&quot; width=&quot;1000&quot; height=&quot;600&quot;>; &lt;figcaption>; &lt;span>;记者2015 年 3 月 30 日，在位于拉脱维亚里加的独立、专注于俄罗斯的 Meduza 办事处工作。&lt;/span>; &lt;span>;摄影：Ints Kalniņš/Reuters&lt;/span>; &lt;/figcaption>; &lt;/figure>; &lt;p>;信中称 TV Rain 的违规行为是“错误的”，同时还称赞这家俄罗斯流亡媒体是“为数不多的真正独立的媒体”之一，在俄罗斯境内保留了大量观众。梅杜扎说，该网络显然是反克里姆林宫并反对入侵乌克兰的。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“我们发表了这封信，拉脱维亚记者也第一次支持我们，”蒂姆琴科说。这也引发了对她自己的组织的一些批评。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;记者认为，正是这种批评可能促使拉脱维亚当局或其他人将 Meduza 作为监视目标。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>; “现在看来，这次黑客攻击很可能是由一些欧洲安全部门实施的。我们不知道是拉脱维亚还是其他国家，但我们在拉脱维亚有更多的[存在]，”科尔帕科夫说。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;拉脱维亚和发生黑客攻击的德国都没有提出调查此事泄露事件已被广泛报道。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;拜登政府已将 NSO 和其他间谍软件公司列入黑名单，称它们对美国国家安全构成威胁。美国国务院发言人在回答《卫报》关于蒂姆琴科遭黑客攻击的问题时表示，谴责对记者的骚扰或法外监视，并声援“致力于揭露克里姆林宫针对俄罗斯的残酷战争的独立俄罗斯记者”。乌克兰”。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;拉脱维亚在保护新闻自由方面总体上享有盛誉。 2022 年国务院人权报告发现“没有可靠的报告”表明政府在没有适当法律授权的情况下监控私人在线通信。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;拉脱维亚驻华盛顿大使馆在一份声明中表示，Meduza 的工作“向俄罗斯提供了客观信息”大使馆表示，“[外交部]不知道对蒂姆琴科女士采取了任何电子监控措施。”它补充说：“拉脱维亚一直为独立的俄罗斯媒体及其工作人员提供安全港。目前有超过 20 家俄罗斯媒体机构在拉脱维亚开展业务。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.dw.com/en/german-police-secretly-bought- nso-pegasus-spyware/a-59113197&quot;>;德国联邦警察 (BKA)&lt;/a>; 于 2019 年成为 NSO 客户，表示不会提供有关秘密措施中使用的功能或工具的信息。&lt;/p>; &lt; p>;这一进展是在 &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/may/09/eu-parliament-report-calls-for-tighter-regulation-of-间谍软件&quot;>;欧洲议会的一个特别委员会&lt;/a>;，负责调查欧洲各国政府（包括匈牙利、西班牙、希腊和波兰）滥用间谍软件的情况。&lt;/p>; &lt;figure data-media-id=&quot;29ba18c5d69b8434f0f1772120334172b002303b&quot;>; &lt;img src =&quot;https://media.guim.co.uk/29ba18c5d69b8434f0f1772120334172b002303b/0_15_4567_2742/1000.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;一名白人妇女，留着又长又厚的红棕色卷发，戴着圆形玳瑁眼镜和蓝色细条纹西装当她站在讲台上的麦克风后面听某人讲话时，她身后是亮蓝色的背景。” width=&quot;1000&quot; height=&quot;600&quot;>; &lt;figcaption>; &lt;span>;2022 年 11 月 8 日，欧洲议会荷兰议员苏菲在比利时布鲁塞尔。&lt;/span>; &lt;span>;摄影：Olivier Hoslet/EPA&lt;/span>; &lt;/figcaption>; &lt;/figure>; &lt;p>;负责调查的荷兰欧洲议会议员 Sophie in &#39;t Veld 对最近的事态发展和明显使用“极权主义策略”表示失望她说，这些国家在欧盟国家内部继续使用 Pegasus 和其他间谍软件工具，而没有受到各国政府或欧盟委员会的任何干预或监督。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“人们经常说，整个间谍软件故事与欧洲版本进行了比较水门事件。它不是。这更像是&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=n3_iLOp6IhM&quot;>;他人的生活&lt;/a>;，”她说，指的是这部描绘无处不在的监控的奥斯卡获奖德国电影20 世纪 80 年代东德的艺术家和作家。&lt;/p>; &lt;aside>; &lt;p>;&lt;span>;相关：&lt;/span>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/technology/2023/sep /13/exiled- Russian-journalist-galina-timchenko-reportedly-hacked-using-nso-group-spyware&quot;>;流亡俄罗斯记者使用 NSO 集团间谍软件遭到黑客攻击&lt;/a>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/aside>; &lt;p>;“我并不是说欧洲已经陷入极权主义，但这些都是极权主义的方法，”她说。 “如果拉脱维亚政府或其他欧洲国家确实这样做了，那就没有办法查明了。没有补救措施，也没有监督。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;她补充道：“[欧盟]政府将其用于政治目的，就像不民主的政府一样。在一些非常特殊的情况下，间谍软件的使用可能是合法的……关键是我们无法知道这种使用是否合理且合法。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;一位知情人士表示，国家统计局已经开设了一个调查此事。该公司过去曾表示，它只向政府机构出售其强大的黑客工具，用于调查严重犯罪。&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Mon, 25 Sep 2023 12:22:01 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Brian Cox on Rupert Murdoch’s succession plan: ‘the freedom to manipulate’]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/media/2023/sep/25/brian-cox-rupert-murdoch-news-corp-exit-comment-joke-succession]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-09-25T02:49:46Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/cd05f964171745f9fcc519cc5ac97313bc56e445/0_0_2500_1500 /master/2500.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=057a64e8cb3063a86e34fef767950e08&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;布莱恩·考克斯和鲁珀特·默多克&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;继任演员布莱恩·考克斯评论了鲁珀特·默多克的 &lt;a href =&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/media/2023/sep/21/rupert-murdoch-stepping-down-chair-fox-news-corp&quot;>;自己的继任计划&lt;/a>;，同时似乎在批评媒体大亨将自己的世界观强加于他人。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;考克斯告诉 BBC，他认为默多克可能花了太多时间观看 HBO 的热门剧集，该剧大量借鉴了默多克王朝的现实生活戏剧。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;金球奖得主考克斯在该剧中饰演家族族长洛根·罗伊，他周末表示&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/media/2023/sep/21/rupert-murdoch- Fox-news-lawsuits-donald-trump&quot;>;默多克宣布&lt;/a>;，他将辞去新闻集团和福克斯董事长的职务，让路&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/media/ 2023/sep/22/what-does-lachlan-murdoch-succession-rupert-mean-news-corp-australia&quot;>;对于他的长子&lt;/a>;来说并不奇怪。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“我认为他是考克斯在谈到默多克决定任命拉克兰代替他的兄弟姐妹伊丽莎白和詹姆斯时说道。&lt;/p>; &lt;aside>; &lt;p>;&lt;span>;相关：&lt;/span>;&lt;a href=&quot;https: //www.theguardian.com/media/2023/sep/23/rupert-murdoch-made-his-own-rules-what-is-the-media-moguls-real-legacy&quot;>;鲁珀特·默多克制定了自己的规则 –这位媒体大亨的真正遗产是什么？&lt;/a>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/aside>; &lt;p>;“他可能是上帝地球上最顽强的人。他只是继续前进，但我认为最终到了某个时刻，他必须停下来，这件事必须发生，而且它已经发生了。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;考克斯说，他怀疑鲁珀特·默多克 92 岁的心理健康状况“相当好......但现在工作量一定太大了”。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;然而，这位演员批评了默多克对新闻自由的解释，他在回应媒体老板上周的声明时说：“为言论自由而战最终，思想自由变得前所未有的强烈。我的父亲（基思·默多克）坚信自由，而拉克兰也绝对致力于这一事业。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;考克斯对默多克的“概括性”声明提出了异议。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“自由？自由是为了什么？将自己的想法强加给他人的自由，或者在某些方向上操纵某些事物的自由？我的意思是，他一生中确实做了很多这样的事，”他告诉 BBC。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;考克斯表示，他的《继任者》角色与默多克有一个关键的不同——虚构的大亨是白手起家的，而真实的大亨则是-后者的生活继承并建立在他父亲的帝国之上。但是，他说，两人都“非常纵容”以达到自己的目的。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;这位七十多岁的演员，&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/stage/2023/sep /20/brian-cox-bach-theatre-the-score&quot;>;目前正在排练&lt;/a>;皇家巴斯剧院制作的奥利弗·科顿的《乐谱》（考克斯将扮演约翰·塞巴斯蒂安·巴赫），拒绝就是否提供意见拉克兰是“肯德尔、罗曼或康纳”。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“我不确定他是谁，因为我有点不参与整个默多克的事情。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“因为当你扮演一个角色，这是你的创造。唯一的共同点是鲁珀特实际上很少表达自己的观点，他让事情[行动]自己说话。”&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Mon, 25 Sep 2023 11:52:02 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Biden seeks to win over Pacific leaders as Solomon Islands turns back on talks]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/sep/25/biden-seeks-to-win-over-pacific-leaders-as-solomon-islands-turns-back-on-talks]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-09-25T03:27:29Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/d62e359a023b251e55d868e440b5018f00af4825/563_76_3298_1979 /master/3298.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=e64f1bbd9023564541b32ef583b4badf&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;美国总统乔·拜登&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;乔·拜登总统本周将在白宫接待太平洋领导人由于对中国在该地区的存在日益担忧，美国寻求加强与各国的接触。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;预计美国将为基础设施和更多海上合作以及为库克群岛和努埃岛设立新大使馆提供资金。但谈判已经遭遇挫折，因为所罗门群岛 &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/sep/24/biden-pacific-summit-suffers-setback-as-solomon-islands- pm-skips-meeting&quot;>;现在与北京关系密切的总理玛纳西·索加瓦雷(Manasseh Sogavare)将不会出席。&lt;/a>;&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“我们对他选择不参加这次非常特别的峰会感到失望，一位白宫官员表示。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;由 18 个成员组成的太平洋岛屿论坛的领导人预计将在周一和周四在白宫举行的会谈中推动对气候变化等问题提供更多支持。星期二。&lt;/p>; &lt;aside>; &lt;p>;&lt;span>;相关：&lt;/span>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/jul/29/pacific-pulling-power- Western-leaders-rush-to-region-in-effort-to counter-china&quot;>;太平洋拉力：西方领导人涌入该地区以对抗中国&lt;/a>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/aside>; &lt;p>;拜登主持了&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2022/sep/28/us-pacific-summit-faces-rocky-start-as-island-leaders-reject-washingtons-offers&quot; >;一年前与 14 个太平洋岛国举行的第一次峰会&lt;/a>;，会上他的政府承诺与盟友和伙伴更加努力地合作，以满足他们的需求。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“毫无疑问，有一些作用中华人民共和国[中国]在这一切中发挥了作用……。法新社援引一位不愿透露姓名的白宫高级官员的话说：“它的自信和影响力，包括在该地区的影响力，一直是要求我们保持战略重点的一个因素。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;主任梅格·基恩博士洛伊研究所太平洋岛屿项目的负责人称这次峰会是“历史性的”，是在拜登之后举行的 &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/may/17/disappointment-in-papua-新几内亚在拜登取消美国领导人首次访问后取消了今年早些时候对巴布亚新几内亚的访问&lt;/a>;，专注于债务上限谈判。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“鉴于长期以来缺席，美国一直在迅速努力收复失地，”基恩说。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“他们已经回到了该地区。该地区正在等待重大承诺是否能够兑现。”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;在 2022 年峰会期间，&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2022/sep/ 29/us-pledges-to-boost-aid-and-diplomacy-in-pacific-as-historic-summit-begins&quot;>;美国宣布向岛国提供超过8亿美元的援助&lt;/a>;。白宫在一份声明中表示，峰会将重申美国对共同区域优先事项以及在气候变化和海事安全等关键问题上进行合作的承诺。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;汤加总理索瓦莱尼告诉记者，即将举行的会议是“一次重要的会议”。上周峰会前在纽约举行的一次高级别会议上，索瓦莱尼表示汤加的首要任务是气候变化和海洋，他将寻求新的投资者支持这些挑战。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“变革的紧迫性是显而易见的，”索瓦莱尼说。&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;索瓦莱尼预计将讨论美国如何支持更好地获得气候融资和改善海洋安全&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;太平洋岛屿论坛秘书长亨利·普纳上周在纽约举行的一次活动中表示，他希望此次峰会能够就气候变化等问题采取具体行动。&lt;/p>; &lt;figure data-media-id=&quot;488ae607771c93c3be6ae83f97e62bf10fe3216c&quot;>; &lt;img src=&quot;https://media.guim.co.uk/488ae607771c93c3be6ae83f97e62bf10fe3216c/512_894_4379_2627/1000.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;Leaders at the US-Pacific Island Country summit in September 2022 .&quot; width=&quot;1000&quot; height=&quot;600&quot;>; &lt;figcaption>; &lt;span>;Leaders at the US-Pacific Island Country summit in September 2022.&lt;/span>; &lt;span>;Photograph: Jonathan Ernst/Reuters&lt;/span>; &lt;/figcaption>; &lt;/figure>; &lt;p>;Puna said the Pacific island region had gone from a period of strategic neglect just a decade ago to become a subject of strategic interest, competition and “manipulation” today – a reference to the geopolitical rivalry for influence in the region between the US and China.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;China &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2022/apr/20/the-deal-that-shocked-the-world-inside-the-china-solomons-security-pact&quot;>;signed a security pact &lt;/a>;with Solomon Islands last year, prompting concern in the US and Australia about Beijing&#39;s ambitions in the region. At the same time, Washington has been stepping up its engagement with the Pacific, with new embassies and &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/may/23/papua-new-guinea-pm-james-marape-antony-blinken-us-png-defence-security-deal&quot;>;high-level visits&lt;/a>;. Earlier this year the US reopened its &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/feb/02/us-opens-embassy-in-solomon-islands-to-counter-china&quot;>;embassy in Solomon Islands after a 30-year absence. &lt;/a>;It also opened an embassy in Tonga and &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/apr/03/us-to-open-embassy-in-vanuatu-as-it-seeks-to-counter-china-in-the-pacific&quot;>;plans one for Vanuatu&lt;/a>;.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;em>;Reuters and Agence France-Presse contributed to this report&lt;/em>;&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Mon, 25 Sep 2023 11:52:02 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Hollywood writers strike: WGA reaches ‘tentative’ deal to end 146-day strike]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/culture/2023/sep/25/hollywood-writers-strike-end-wga-deal-details-negotiations]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-09-25T02:52:37Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/9d9945b8cf4668ed2eed8974edddb7f179ab4b44/0_78_9216_5530/master/9216.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=1d64c2d1d3bf8959489b2a1e367285dc&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;Members of both WGA and Sag-Aftra rally at Paramount Studios in Los Angeles on 13 September.&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;Hollywood writers are poised to end their nearly five-month strike after reaching a tentative agreement with studios, the writers&#39; union and the Alliance of Motion Picture and Television Producers said Sunday night, though the full details of agreement still have to be formally approved.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The deal came after five marathon days of renewed talks by negotiators for the Writers Guild of America (WGA) and an alliance of studios, streaming services and production companies, and must be approved by the guild&#39;s board and members before the strike officially ends.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The terms of the deal were not immediately announced, but the WGA called the deal “exceptional – with meaningful gains and protections for writers in every sector of the membership,” in an email to members of its negotiating committee, &lt;a href=&quot;https://variety.com/2023/biz/news/writers-strike-ends-wga-amptp-deal-2-1235733452/&quot;>;Variety reported&lt;/a>;.&lt;/p>; &lt;figure data-canonical-url=&quot;https://twitter.com/WGAWest/status/1706136145019683010&quot;>; &lt;blockquote>; &lt;p>;The WGA and AMPTP have reached a tentative agreement. This was made possible by the enduring solidarity of WGA members and extraordinary support of our union siblings who stood with us for over 146 days. More details coming after contract language is finalized. &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/hashtag/WGAStrike?src=hash&amp;amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&quot;>;#WGAStrike&lt;/a>; &lt;a href=&quot;https://t.co/GBg2wZBwGB&quot;>;pic.twitter.com/GBg2wZBwGB&lt;/a>;&lt;/p>;— Writers Guild of America West (@WGAWest) &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/WGAWest/status/1706136145019683010?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&quot;>;September 25, 2023&lt;/a>; &lt;/blockquote>; &lt;/figure>; &lt;p>;The agreement comes just five days before the strike would&#39;ve broken the record of the union&#39;s 1988 strike to become the longest in the guild&#39;s history, and the longest Hollywood strike in decades. Union leaders are expected to vote on the full terms of the new three-year contract on Tuesday, Variety reported.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Late-night television shows are expected to resume production, and could even return to the air within days, but Hollywood actors, who joined the industry&#39;s historic “double strike” in July, remain on strike, meaning that many new film and television projects are expected to stay on hold.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The writers&#39; strike was driven by Hollywood workers&#39; frustrations with their share of the profits in an online-streaming era, and spotlighted artists&#39; concerns about the threats artificial intelligence might pose to their industry. While Bob Iger, the Disney CEO, called the writers&#39; and actors&#39; demands “&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.latimes.com/entertainment-arts/business/story/2023-07-13/disney-bob-iger-says-actors-strike-writers-strike-unrealistic&quot;>;just not realistic&lt;/a>;” in July, the strike ultimately highlighted the solidarity among unions within Hollywood - and the broad public support for workers&#39; demands, as the Tinseltown labor disputes kicked off a “hot labor summer” of strikes across &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/business/video/2023/sep/15/were-not-asking-to-be-millionaires-workers-strike-at-us-car-giants-video&quot;>;multiple industries&lt;/a>;.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;During a hot summer, striking actors and writers have marched together outside studios across Los Angeles, from Amazon to Warner Bros to Disney. To improve morale, some of the picketers have come dressed in themed costumes of the day, like on “Bridgerton Day” outside Netflix&#39;s studios.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;A-list Hollywood actors made their support for the strikes clear even before the actors&#39; union had authorized a strike. Some wealthy directors and producers announced &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/general-news/ryan-murphy-strike-fund-cast-crews-hollywood-strikes-1235585581/&quot;>;six-figure donations&lt;/a>; to strike funds to support former cast and crew members, while other stars &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/film/2023/sep/14/strike-hollywood-crew-ebay-auction&quot;>;auctioned off Zoom meetings &lt;/a>;and one-on-one experiences to raise money for a crew healthcare fund.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The few celebrities who attempted to flout strike rules – including Drew Barrymore, who announced she would resume her popular talkshow &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.latimes.com/entertainment-arts/tv/story/2023-09-11/drew-barrymore-show-backlash-picket-writers-strike-wga&quot;>;while her writers were still on strike&lt;/a>; – faced broad public condemnation, and quickly &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/culture/2023/sep/18/drew-barrymore-postpones-talk-show-return-writers-strike-backlash&quot;>;reversed course&lt;/a>;.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;em>;The Associated Press contributed reporting&lt;/em>;&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Mon, 25 Sep 2023 11:22:01 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Canada’s house speaker apologises after praising Ukrainian veteran who fought for Nazis]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/sep/25/canadas-house-speaker-apologises-after-praising-ukrainian-veteran-who-fought-for-nazis]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-09-25T02:43:21Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/18f27f0909d8b5b76f1d85ff071401d061d3a713/0_139_5000_3002/master/5000.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=897748ca983b6766ba96f3b0d2218d6e&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;Anthony Rota, Speaker of the House of Commons in Canada. &lt;/div>;&lt;p>;The speaker of Canada&#39;s House of Commons has apologised for praising an individual at a parliamentary meeting who fought for a Nazi military unit during the second world war.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Just after Ukrainian president Volodymyr Zelenskiy delivered an address to the Canadian parliament on Friday, lawmakers gave 98-year-old Yaroslav Hunka a standing ovation when speaker Anthony Rota drew attention to him. Rota introduced Hunka as a war hero who fought for the First Ukrainian Division.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“In my remarks following the address of the president of Ukraine, I recognised an individual in the gallery. I have subsequently become aware of more information which causes me to regret my decision to do so,” Rota said in a statement.&lt;/p>; &lt;aside>; &lt;p>;&lt;span>;Related: &lt;/span>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/sep/22/zelenskiy-trudeau-canada-parliament-ukraine-war-russia&quot;>;Zelenskiy urges Canada to stay with Ukraine as he speaks to parliament&lt;/a>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/aside>; &lt;p>;He added that his fellow parliament members and the Ukraine delegation were not aware of his plan to recognise Hunka. Rota noted Hunka is from his district.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“I particularly want to extend my deepest apologies to Jewish communities in Canada and around the world. I accept full responsibility for my action,” Rota said.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Hunka could not be immediately reached for comment.&lt;/p>; &lt;figure data-media-id=&quot;3c7b1b1454a17bdcd95699b470d4de4fd9734f50&quot;>; &lt;img src=&quot;https://media.guim.co.uk/3c7b1b1454a17bdcd95699b470d4de4fd9734f50/0_0_3000_2124/1000.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;Yaroslav Hunka waits for the arrival of Ukrainian president Volodymyr Zelenskiy in the House of Commons.&quot; width=&quot;1000&quot; height=&quot;708&quot;>; &lt;figcaption>; &lt;span>;Yaroslav Hunka waits for the arrival of Ukrainian president Volodymyr Zelenskiy in the House of Commons.&lt;/span>; &lt;span>;Photograph: Patrick Doyle/AP&lt;/span>; &lt;/figcaption>; &lt;/figure>; &lt;p>;Canadian lawmakers cheered and Zelenskiy raised his fist in acknowledgment as Hunka saluted from the gallery during two separate standing ovations. Rota called him a “Ukrainian hero and a Canadian hero, and we thank him for all his service.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Zelenskiy was in Ottawa to bolster support from western allies for Ukraine&#39;s fight against the Russian invasion. Vladimir Putin has painted his enemies in Ukraine as “neo-Nazis,” even though Zelenskiy is Jewish and lost relatives in the Holocaust.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Prime minister Justin Trudeau&#39;s office said in a statement that Rota had apologised and accepted full responsibility for issuing the invitation to Hunka and for the recognition in parliament.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“This was the right thing to do,” the statement said. “No advance notice was provided to the prime minister&#39;s office, nor the Ukrainian delegation, about the invitation or the recognition.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The First Ukrainian Division was also known as the Waffen-SS Galicia Division or the SS 14th Waffen Division, a voluntary unit that was under the command of the Nazis.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The Friends of Simon Wiesenthal Center for Holocaust Studies issued a statement Sunday saying the division “was responsible for the mass murder of innocent civilians with a level of brutality and malice that is unimaginable.”&lt;/p>; &lt;figure data-media-id=&quot;2bd4a3dcb6dbfe41c38139e5e26318d79e5e4dea&quot;>; &lt;img src=&quot;https://media.guim.co.uk/2bd4a3dcb6dbfe41c38139e5e26318d79e5e4dea/0_0_6000_4220/1000.jpg&quot; alt=&quot;Ukrainian president Volodymyr Zelinsky and Canada&#39;s prime minister Justin Trudeau recognise Yaroslav Hunka.&quot; width=&quot;1000&quot; height=&quot;703&quot;>; &lt;figcaption>; &lt;span>;Ukrainian president Volodymyr Zelinsky and Canada&#39;s prime minister Justin Trudeau recognise Yaroslav Hunka.&lt;/span>; &lt;span>;Photograph: Patrick Doyle/AP&lt;/span>; &lt;/figcaption>; &lt;/figure>; &lt;p>;“An apology is owed to every Holocaust survivor and veteran of the second world war who fought the Nazis, and an explanation must be provided as to how this individual entered the hallowed halls of Canadian parliament and received recognition from the Speaker of the House and a standing ovation,” the statement said.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Michael Mostyn, the head of Jewish human rights organization B&#39;nai Brith Canada, said it was outrageous that parliament had honored a former member of a Nazi unit.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Members of parliament from all parties rose to applaud Hunka. A spokesperson for the Conservative party said the party was not aware of his history at the time.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“We find the reports of this individual&#39;s history very troubling,” said Sebastian Skamski, adding that Trudeau&#39;s Liberal party would have to explain why he was invited.&lt;/p>;&lt;br>;&lt;hr>;&lt;div>;获取更多RSS：&lt;br>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://feedx.net&quot; style=&quot;color:orange&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>;https://feedx.net&lt;/a>; &lt;br>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://feedx.best&quot; style=&quot;color:orange&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>;https://feedx.best&lt;/a>;&lt;br>;&lt;/div>;</description><pubDate> Mon, 25 Sep 2023 10:52:01 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[New Zealand election: Luxon says National open to NZ First coalition]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/sep/25/new-zealand-election-luxon-says-national-open-to-nz-first-coalition]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-09-25T01:05:16Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/e1575e1760a74e69b57344bd442c803d4ba49d28/787_0_4610_2765/master/4610.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=8b96d30e064f75c18a33ae0f9c10dead&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;National leader Christopher Luxon.&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;After months of prevarication, National leader Christopher Luxon has said he will pursue a coalition with Winston Peters&#39; New Zealand First after the October election, but only as a last resort.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Luxon even left open the prospect of a sensational return for Peters as deputy prime minister in declaring himself open to a deal with the politician.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The National leader said in a video posted to social media that his preference was to form a strong and stable two-party coalition government between his party and Act.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;However, he added he would be prepared to form a coalition with NZ First if that would get his party into power.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Coalitions are the norm under New Zealand&#39;s electoral system and only once since the system was introduced in 1996 has a party been able to govern alone.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;New Zealand will hold its election on 14 October, with polls &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/sep/13/guardian-essential-new-zealand-poll-winston-peters-in-position-to-become-election-kingmaker&quot;>;pointing towards a change after two terms of Labour-led government&lt;/a>;, to the centre-right National party.&lt;/p>; &lt;aside>; &lt;p>;&lt;span>;Related: &lt;/span>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/sep/22/how-david-seymour-hopes-to-move-new-zealand-to-the-right&quot;>;How David Seymour hopes to move New Zealand to the right&lt;/a>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/aside>; &lt;p>;However, the same polls show National falling short of a majority and needing at least one other party to govern, with right-wing libertarians Act and Peters&#39; populists NZ First on the menu for Luxon in post-election negotiations.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“My strong preference is to form a strong and stable two party coalition government between National and Act,” Luxon said.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“I believe that government would be in the best interests of New Zealanders at this very uncertain time.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“However, if New Zealand First is returned to parliament and I need to pick up the phone to Peters … I will make that call.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Luxon had been peppered with questions about whether he would work with NZ First for months, having already ruled out left-leaning and far-right fringe parties.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;On Newstalk ZB, Luxon said he declared his hand due to his view that a change of government was desperately needed.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“Labour&#39;s record is abysmal in three years with an absolute majority and God help us if they end up going with Te Pati Māori and the Greens,” he said.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“We&#39;d all be packing up and leaving.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The decision changes the dynamic of the election campaign, which will shift to the possibilities of how a National-Act-NZ First coalition could govern.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;While National and Act are aligned on key issues, NZ First is opposed to their centrepiece promise for tax cuts, which Peters says New Zealand cannot afford.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;It is not yet clear whether NZ First will be in parliament: parties need to win at least 5% of the vote to return MPs in New Zealand, and the party is polling at around that threshold.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;em>;Australian Associated Press and Reuters contributed to this report&lt;/em>;&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Mon, 25 Sep 2023 09:22:01 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Seven months after entering hospice care Jimmy Carter visits peanut festival]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/sep/25/jimmy-carter-visits-plains-peanut-festival-georgia]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-09-24T23:51:19Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/c3d9730e54b163f880b1d2ba77061154a9ca671b/0_99_3255_1953/master/3255.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=e306d425a6f4ced7f10ff208341c8279&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;Former US president Jimmy Carter.&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;Former president Jimmy Carter and his wife, Rosalynn, have made a surprise appearance at a peanut festival in their Georgia home town, the Carter Center wrote in a social media post on X, formerly known as Twitter.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The former president, who was also once a peanut farmer, and his wife are seen in a video riding through the Plains Peanut Festival in a black SUV.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“Beautiful day for President &amp;amp; Mrs. Carter to enjoy a ride through the Plains Peanut Festival! And just a week before he turns 99,” the Carter Center wrote on X after sharing the video taken by a spectator.&lt;/p>; &lt;figure data-canonical-url=&quot;https://twitter.com/CarterCenter/status/1705614230370541856&quot;>; &lt;blockquote>; &lt;p>;Beautiful day for President &amp;amp; Mrs. Carter to enjoy a ride through the Plains Peanut Festival! And just a week before he turns 99.&lt;br>;&lt;br>; We&#39;re betting peanut butter ice cream is on the menu for lunch!&lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/hashtag/JimmyCarter99?src=hash&amp;amp;ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&quot;>;#JimmyCarter99&lt;/a>; &lt;a href=&quot;https://t.co/c3b9OqzjXU&quot;>;https://t.co/c3b9OqzjXU&lt;/a>;&lt;/p>;— The Carter Center (@CarterCenter) &lt;a href=&quot;https://twitter.com/CarterCenter/status/1705614230370541856?ref_src=twsrc%5Etfw&quot;>;September 23, 2023&lt;/a>; &lt;/blockquote>; &lt;/figure>; &lt;p>;The former president is 98 and &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/feb/19/jimmy-carter-hospice-care-tributes-reaction&quot;>;has been in home hospice care since February&lt;/a>;. 10 月 1 日，他就满 99 岁了。 The former first lady &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/may/30/rosalynn-carter-diagnosed-with-dementia&quot;>;has since been diagnosed with dementia&lt;/a>;. The couple this summer marked their 77th wedding anniversary, extending their record as the nation&#39;s longest-married first couple.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“It was amazing considering that he is in hospice care, and he is tough enough to come out here. In my opinion, he is one of the toughest men to serve as President, and he is my favorite,” Reed Elliotte, a Corbin, Kentucky resident, told WALB-TV.&lt;/p>; &lt;aside>; &lt;p>;&lt;span>;Related: &lt;/span>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/mar/14/joe-biden-jimmy-carter-eulogy&quot;>;Joe Biden says Jimmy Carter has asked him to deliver his eulogy&lt;/a>;&lt;/p>; &lt;/aside>; &lt;p>;Carter, a one-term Democrat who left office in 1981, has lived longer after leaving the White House than any former president in US history.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;In recent years, he has suffered from several health issues including melanoma that spread to his liver and brain, although he was said to have responded well to treatment.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Last month their grandson, Josh Carter, &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2023/aug/20/jimmy-carter-rosalynn-carter-final-chapter-grandson-says&quot;>;said the former first couple were “still holding hands”&lt;/a>; but that it was clear they were “in the final chapter”.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;&lt;em>;Associated Press and Reuters contributed to this report&lt;/em>;&lt;/p>;&lt;br>;&lt;hr>;&lt;div>;获取更多RSS：&lt;br>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://feedx.net&quot; style=&quot;color:orange&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>;https://feedx.net&lt;/a>; &lt;br>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://feedx.best&quot; style=&quot;color:orange&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>;https://feedx.best&lt;/a>;&lt;br>;&lt;/div>;</description><pubDate> Mon, 25 Sep 2023 08:22:01 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Lego abandons effort to make bricks from recycled plastic bottles]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2023/sep/24/lego-abandons-effort-to-make-bricks-from-recycled-plastic-bottles]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-09-24T22:40:34Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/e451fcf9d9ce567c9eaf24dcc538213ea6db4323/0_148_5196_3119/master/5196.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=b2cd44f88d020e307a4b60e6a4fdef35&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;A jumble of Lego bricks&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;Lego has stopped a project to make bricks from recycled drinks bottles instead of oil-based plastic, saying it would have led to higher carbon emissions over the product&#39;s lifetime.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The move, &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.ft.com/content/6cad1883-f87a-471d-9688-c1a3c5a0b7dc&quot;>;first reported by the Financial Times&lt;/a>;, followed efforts by the world&#39;s largest toymaker &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/lifeandstyle/2021/jun/23/lego-develops-first-bricks-made-of-recycled-plastic-bottles&quot;>;to research more sustainable materials&lt;/a>;, as part of a wave of companies reassessing their contribution to global emissions as the &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.theguardian.com/environment/2023/aug/28/dramatic-climate-action-needed-curtail-extreme-weather&quot;>;climate crisis hits&lt;/a>;.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The Danish company makes billions of Lego pieces a year, and in 2021 began researching a potential transition to recycled polyethylene terephthalate (PET) from acrylonitrile butadiene styrene (ABS), which needs about 2kg of petroleum to make 1kg of plastic. ABS is used in about 80% of Lego blocks.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“It&#39;s like trying to make a bike out of wood rather than steel,” said Tim Brooks, Lego&#39;s head of sustainability, referring to how the non-oil-based material was softer and demanded extra ingredients for durability, as well as greater energy for processing and drying.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The “level of disruption to the manufacturing environment was such that we needed to change everything in our factories” to scale up recycled PET use, he said. “毕竟，碳足迹会更高。 It was disappointing.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The company said in 2021 it had more than 150 people working on sustainability. But Lego&#39;s chief executive, Niels Christiansen, told the FT the toymaker “tested hundreds and hundreds of materials” but could not find a “magic material” to solve sustainability issues.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Instead, Lego aims to make each part of ABS more sustainable by incorporating more bio-based and recycled material. Christiansen said the group will triple spending on sustainability to $3bn (£2.45bn) a year by 2025 while promising not to pass on higher costs to consumers.&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Mon, 25 Sep 2023 07:22:02 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[Political outsider Stefanos Kasselakis wins race to lead Greece’s Syriza]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.theguardian.com/world/2023/sep/24/political-outsider-stefanos-kasselakis-wins-race-to-lead-greeces-syriza]]><description> &lt;div>;&lt;i>;2023-09-24T22:41:50Z&lt;/i>;&lt;/div>;&lt;div>;&lt;img src=&quot;https://i.guim.co.uk/img/media/0a8f59296c73497dd1ffd7ccc56b2da23c6a5e78/0_479_7847_4711/master/7847.jpg?w=600&amp;fit=bounds&amp;sig-ignores-params=true&amp;s=278117b36d4f0aabf086b8ee3937f410&quot; alt=&quot;&quot;>;Stefanos Kasselakis waves to supporters outside the party&#39;s headquarters&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;Stefanos Kasselakis, an outsider with no previous experience of politics in Greece, has emerged the victor of an electric race to lead the leftwing Syriza, the country&#39;s main opposition party.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The Greek-American entrepreneur, who announced his candidacy for the post barely four weeks ago, attained 56.69% of the vote against 43.31% for Efi Achtsioglou, a former labour minister who had long been viewed as the favourite. Kasselakis&#39; win now makes him one of the most powerful people in Greece.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Amid jubilant scenes outside Syriza&#39;s headquarters in Athens, the 35-year-old told supporters: “Today light won and hope collectively, hope for the future … I am not a phenomenon.我是社会的代言人，我不会让你们失望的。 Tomorrow the hard work begins.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;A shipping executive in the US, Kasselakis stepped into the race when Aléxis Tsípras, the party&#39;s president for the past 15 years, announced he would be stepping down after Syriza&#39;s double defeat in general elections held in May and June. The prime minister from 2015 to 2019, Tsipras had kept a “neutral” stance, refusing to endorse either candidate after Kasselakis&#39; unexpected win in the first round last week.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;As the results rolled in late Sunday, the businessman&#39;s victory was described as both stunning and unprecedented.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Some 133,600 voters cast ballots at an estimated 537 polling stations nationwide with Syriza cadres describing the turnout as not only impressive but indicative of the desire to see a newly reinvigorated and strong opposition party facing a government intent on demolishing hard-won rights.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Kasselakis, who is not known to have had any links with Syriza before this year, moved to Athens only months ago, settling in the capital with his American husband Tyler McBeth.他向受过培训的护士麦克贝斯喊话，加入他向人群发表讲话，称他的伴侣为“我的私人家人”。 “Thank you from the bottom of my heart for welcoming him and embracing him,” he said smiling as supporters shouted “Stefanos change everything”.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The Greek-American has signalled that he will apply root-and-branch change to Syriza, a progressive alliance that includes Marxists, Euro-communists, ecologists and social democrats. He has stated that if the party ever wants to taste power again it should “just copy the US formula as soon as possible” by transforming into a “big tent” US-style Democratic party.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;“This is the end of leftwing Syriza as we know it,” Stelios Kouloglou, a Syriza MEP told the Guardian. “那个派对今晚就死了。卡塞拉基斯将做出巨大的改变，未来将进行案例研究，因为他所取得的成就是如此令人惊叹。他几乎凭空出现，现在掌权了。 It&#39;s crazy, a scenario that no one would have believed a few months ago.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Traditional leftists in the party, he said, were in “complete shock”.&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;Confirming that changes were inevitable, Evangelos Antonaros a former MP with the ruling centre-right New Democracy party, who ran with Syriza at Tsípras&#39; request in May, said: “We support Kasselakis because he wants to move the party towards the centre, the ground that Syriza lost in the last election. It will be re-established with open minds and open doors.”&lt;/p>; &lt;p>;The new Syriza leader has repeatedly said that he is better placed to defeat prime minister Kyriakos Mitsotakis, citing what he has described as his “better English and finance and business” knowledge.&lt;/p>;&lt;br>;&lt;hr>;&lt;div>;获取更多RSS：&lt;br>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://feedx.net&quot; style=&quot;color:orange&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>;https://feedx.net&lt;/a>; &lt;br>;&lt;a href=&quot;https://feedx.best&quot; style=&quot;color:orange&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot;>;https://feedx.best&lt;/a>;&lt;br>;&lt;/div>;</description><pubDate> Mon, 25 Sep 2023 07:22:02 +0800</pubDate></item></channel></rss>